      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for primary QoI (shear stress scalar used in hemolysis power law) must be less than 5% on the medium mesh.",
      "rationale": "Three-mesh Richardson extrapolation performed at the 6 LPM / 3500 RPM operating point. GCI fine = 1.8%, GCI medium = 3.4% for volume-averaged shear stress. Medium mesh (7.2 M hexahedral elements) adopted as production mesh. Asymptotic convergence ratio confirms grid independence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) must be documented and replicated in simulation boundary conditions within stated measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "PIV benchmark test conditions (flow rates 2.5–7 LPM, speed 2000–4500 RPM, 40% glycerol–water blood analog, T = 22 ± 0.5 °C) are fully documented in the FDA benchmark protocol. Simulation boundary conditions match within 1.2% for flow rate and 0.3% for rotational speed. Fluid viscosity assigned from published Newtonian fit."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (GVM or equivalent) must demonstrate acceptable agreement between simulation and experiment for velocity fields and hemolysis index.",
      "rationale": "Velocity field GVM = 0.94 across all operating points versus PIV data. Relative hemolysis index mean absolute error = 0.07 RH units across 5 operating points versus in vitro predicate data. Both metrics satisfy MRL 2 acceptance thresholds. Comparison documented in validation report VR-2025-04."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (velocity magnitude, shear stress, RH index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (pump-induced hemolysis) and the regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH) derived from the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model applied to CFD shear-stress and exposure-time fields. RH < 1 is the regulatory acceptance criterion per FDA guidance. Velocity fields are a secondary QoI confirming flow physics fidelity. Relevance is direct and well-established in the literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
