      "rationale": "Launder–Sharma low-Reynolds-number k-ε model selected based on published benchmark studies for confined rotating flows. Model form uncertainty not formally quantified at MRL 2. Selection rationale documented in simulation plan SP-2024-11."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be traceable to measurement data or published sources with stated uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Pump geometry sourced from calibrated CMM measurements (±0.01 mm). Fluid properties (density, viscosity) from published Newtonian fit to 40% glycerol–water at 22 °C. Inlet flow rate and rotational speed from experimental test reports with stated measurement uncertainty. All inputs traceable and within MRL 2 documentation requirements. The in vitro hemolysis reference dataset (dataVintage 2025-02-24) was used to set the RH acceptance threshold; the model revision on 2025-03-17 recalibrated turbulence closure constants but was judged by the assessment team as not materially affecting the hemolysis transport scalar, and no formal re-validation of model inputs against the post-revision model was conducted."
